## 1. Introduction

### 1.1 Purpose

This test plan covers the “Mark Reviewed” feature added to the KB Web Viewer Dashboard and Browser Entry Detail panel. The feature is frontend-only (vanilla JS) calling an existing backend API.

### 1.2 Test Objectives

* Verify all 4 user stories from BRD are implemented correctly
* Validate all 14 business rules (BR-01 through BR-14) are enforced
* Ensure accessibility requirements (keyboard nav, ARIA, contrast) are met
* Confirm error handling for all exception flows (EF-01 through EF-04)
* Verify basePath compliance for API calls

### 1.3 References

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Document | Location |
| BRD | BRD-v1-KSA-108.docx |
| FSD | FSD-v1-KSA-108.docx |
| TDD | TDD-v1-KSA-108.docx |

## 2. Test Strategy

### 2.1 Test Levels

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Level | Scope | Responsibility | Tools |
| Unit Testing (UT) | Individual JS functions (markReviewed, showToast, decrementStaleCount) | Developer | Manual / Browser console |
| Integration Testing (IT) | Frontend ↔ Backend API round-trip | QA | Browser DevTools + live server |
| E2E-UI | Full user workflow in browser | QA | Manual (browser) |
| SIT | Cross-browser, keyboard, screen reader | QA | Manual + axe DevTools |

### 2.2 Test Types

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Type | Description | Applicable |
| Functional Testing | Verify mark reviewed, toast, row removal, badge | Yes |
| Regression Testing | Ensure dashboard load, browser tab still work | Yes |
| Performance Testing | Button click → feedback < 100ms, API < 500ms | Yes |
| Security Testing | XSS prevention in toast, same-origin enforcement | Yes |
| Usability Testing | Keyboard navigation, ARIA labels, color contrast | Yes |
| Compatibility Testing | Chrome, Firefox, Edge (latest 2 versions) | Yes |

### 2.3 Test Approach

* **Manual testing** for UI interactions (click, keyboard, visual feedback)
* **Browser DevTools** for network inspection (API calls, response codes)
* **axe DevTools** for accessibility audit
* **Network throttling** for testing loading states and error scenarios
* Risk-based: prioritize happy path + error handling over edge cases

### 2.4 Entry Criteria

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Level | Entry Criteria |
| UT | Code changes merged to feature branch |
| IT | Server running locally with SQLite DB containing test entries |
| SIT | All UT + IT passed, deployed to test environment |

### 2.5 Exit Criteria

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Level | Exit Criteria |
| UT | All functions return expected results |
| IT | API calls succeed, DOM updates correctly |
| SIT | 100% test cases executed, 0 Critical defects, ≤1 Major defect |

